Image 61 of 61 San Antonio Spurs hung out with Zac Efron, Seth Rogan and Rose Bryne in Atlanta 1 / 61 Back to Gallery In the latest installation of Spurs doing cool things, a few of the boys hung out with the cast of Neighbors 2 Wednesday night.
Tony Parker and Hollywood heartthrob, Zac Efron, standing side-by-side made a handsome picture for eyes on social media to feast upon.
No. 9 tweeted a group photo of himself on the set of Neighbors 2, with Boris Diaw, Efron and Rose Byrne – one of his “favorite actresses.”
Efron, who plays a fraternity brother in the sequel, ended the night with a Coach Pop joke.
RELATED: Tiago Splitter eats with former Spurs teammates Parker, Duncan, Bonner, Diaw ahead of Hawks game
“Welcome, this year’s starting lineup for the Spurs,” he captioned a tweet with a picture of himself with costars, Seth Rogan and Ike Barinholtz, Diaw and Parker. “What will pop think of next.”
The Spurs were in Atlanta, where Neighbors 2 is in production, on Wednesday for their game against the Hawks. The Georgia trip was unsuccessful in terms of preseason records, but the Silver and Black was able to squeeze in bonding time. As well as having a brush with Hollywood, they caught up with former teammate, Tiago Splitter, for a pregame meal before facing off on the court.
And they said the Spurs were boring.
They will take on the Detroit Pistons on Sunday for their first home game, at the renovated AT&T Center's grand opening.
